+`/uav/target_position` is implemented by Demo 04. The remaining topics below
+are recommended contracts for the next implementation step.
+
+## Coordinate Convention
+
+Use the PX4 local NED frame for all `/uav/*` position topics:
+
+| Axis | Meaning | Unit |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| `x` | North / forward from local origin | m |
+| `y` | East / right from local origin | m |
+| `z` | Down from local origin | m |
+
+PX4 local position and `px4_msgs/msg/TrajectorySetpoint` also use NED, so the
+bridge can map most position fields directly.
+
+External modules often reason about height as positive altitude above the local
+origin. In that case:
+
+```text
+z_ned = -altitude
+altitude = -z_ned
+```
+
+Example: a target 2 m above the local origin is `altitude=2.0` and
+`z_ned=-2.0`.
+
+## Recommended Topics
+
+| Topic | Type | Direction | Status | Purpose |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| `/uav/target_position` | `geometry_msgs/msg/Point` | client -> UAV bridge | Implemented in Demo 04 | Position-only target in local NED. |
+| `/uav/target_pose` | `geometry_msgs/msg/PoseStamped` | client -> UAV bridge | Future | Position plus desired yaw. Roll and pitch should be ignored by the bridge. |
+| `/uav/current_position` | `geometry_msgs/msg/PointStamped` | UAV bridge -> clients | Future | Current filtered local NED position. |
+| `/uav/current_target` | `geometry_msgs/msg/PointStamped` | UAV bridge -> clients | Future | Sanitized target currently being sent to PX4. |
+| `/uav/reached_target` | `std_msgs/msg/Bool` | UAV bridge -> clients | Future | `true` when the current target is reached within configured tolerances. |
+| `/uav/control_state` | `std_msgs/msg/String` | UAV bridge -> clients | Future | Human-readable control state such as `IDLE`, `TRACKING`, `REACHED`, `HOLDING`, `LANDING`, `E_STOP`, or `INVALID_TARGET`. |
+| `/uav/emergency_stop` | `std_msgs/msg/Bool` | client -> UAV bridge | Future | `true` requests an immediate safety stop action. |
